This claim is a **counterfactual** — it describes a hypothetical scenario ("If... had adopted a year-round academic calendar, its average daily attendance **would have** increased by at least 3%"). The database records what actually happened, not what would have happened under different conditions.

Per the workflow rules, counterfactual claims are always classified as **NOT ENOUGH INFO**.
